                                                                                        <div class="text testimonial_rotator_description">
                                                                                            <h2 class="testimonial_rotator_slide_title">Protégé Matt Lozada</h2>
                                                                                            <div class="testimonial_rotator_quote">
                                                                                                As a Filipino-American, to be able to sit across highly successful Asian-Americans hailing from Bangladesh, Japan, South Korea, Vietnam, China, Laos, Singapore, Taiwan, Thailand, Cambodia and many other Asian countries was a highly inspiring and incredibly powerful experience. To hear stories from my fellow Asian and Asian-American colleagues who came to this country to pursue their vision of what the American dream could look like to them - whether that be to start their own company, innovate a new technology or change public policy, was an experience that is as valuable as it is rare in today's discussion of what success looks like in the face of adversity that arises from prejudices that come as a consequence of being an ethnic minority in this country. I was both, personally and professionally helped after hearing the testimonies of my fellow entrepreneurs and being able to sit down and have meaningful conversations with them is an experience that can rarely be replicated somewhere else.
                                                                                            </div>
